The paper focuses on developing a machine learning approach to judge the validity of invariants in software systems, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the use of deep neural models (cs.LG) and gated graph neural networks (cs.SY) for this purpose. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Daikon, a dynamic invariant detection tool (cs.PL), and the generation of labeled invariants using large test-suites (cs.AI).
